h2 Error prevention (Legal, Financial, Data)
div.chi-grid
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-breadcrumb
      ol.-text--normal
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20" rel="noopener" target="_blank") WCAG 2.0 Guideline
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/#minimize-error" rel="noopener" target="_blank") 3.3 Input assistance
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/#minimize-error-reversible" rel="noopener" target="_blank") 3.3.4 Error Prevention (Legal, Financial, Data)
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .-lh--3
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs(data-tooltip="Users must be able to understand the information as well as the operation of the user interface." data-position="bottom")
        span Understandable
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs.-ml--1(data-tooltip="Requirements must be satisfied to pass WCAG 2.0 Level AA Success Criteria." data-position="bottom")
        span Level AA
  .chi-col.-w--12
    p.-text
      | <strong>Benefits:</strong> All disabilities.
    p.-text
      | For Web pages that cause legal commitments or financial transactions for the user to occur, that modify or delete user-controllable data in data storage systems, or that submit user test responses, at least one of the following is true:
    ul.-text
      li <strong>Reversible:</strong> Submissions are reversible.
      li <strong>Checked:</strong> Data entered by the user is checked for input errors and the user is provided an opportunity to correct them.
      li <strong>Confirmed:</strong> A mechanism is available for reviewing, confirming, and correcting information before finalizing the submission.
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-card.-s--1.-rounded.-mb--3.-mt--1
      .chi-card__header
        .chi-card__title
          | How to pass
      .chi-card__content.-px--3
        ul.accessibility-checklist
          li 
            | Can the user correct a mistake to avoid the serious consequences as the result of an action that cannot be reversed?
          li 
            | Are safeguards provided to avoid mistakes that can have serious consequences?
          li 
            | Can the user review, correct, confirm before submitting or deleting?
          li 
            | Is success feedback provided when data is submitted successfully?

